  "placement_highlights": "PSG College of Technology maintains a strong reputation for graduate employment, consistently attracting a wide array of top-tier recruiters from diverse sectors. For the most recent placement cycle (estimated 2023), the highest package reached an estimated 40 LPA, with the average package standing at approximately 7.5 LPA and the median at 6.5 LPA. The overall placement rate is estimated to be around 90%. Key recruiting sectors include Information Technology & Software, Core Engineering (encompassing manufacturing, automotive, electrical, and mechanical), Consulting & Analytics, and Electronics & Communication. Prominent companies like TCS, Wipro, Infosys, Amazon, Microsoft, L&T, Siemens, Deloitte, and Qualcomm are regular visitors to the campus, offering roles across various disciplines. The college's robust industry connections and focus on practical, industry-relevant education contribute significantly to these strong placement outcomes. While specific year-on-year breakdowns for gender-based and detailed sector-wise placements are not readily available from general knowledge, the college is known for its inclusive placement process.",
